==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*snuzaz'', from Indo-European ''*snusós''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[snore]], Middle Dutch [[snare]] (Dutch [[snaar]]), Old High German [[snur]], Old Norse [[snor]].  The IE root is also the source of Greek [[νυός]], Latin [[nurus]], Slavic ''*snъxa'' (Russian [[сноха]]), Albanian [[nuse]].

